{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"754cc1ce-0a36-4913-918f-0e03b015cada","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually with `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation. Would you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"790ccda2-c151-4c3f-864e-1eee141634ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question. Let me check if there's anything in the current working directory that might give context, but based on the question, they're likely asking about .NET Web API templates.\n\nLet me just answer this from my knowledge - this is a general knowledge question, not something that requires tool usage.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"7404:287A49:1B3639B:1E36963:69FA8F7F"},"id":"734408d9-3f1b-4c0c-ab93-4388c8a02f52","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:47:04.674Z","parentId":"cfc45886-de6a-4be3-836d-382a9803cce2"}
